qas.question: In what year was the Regierungsbezirk Zichenau annexed?
What other parts of East Prussia were transferred after the annexation of Zichenau?

answers.text: Suwałki to Regierungsbezirk Gumbinnen and Soldau to Regierungsbezirk Allenstein

qas.question: Despite all the propaganda that ws presented to the East Prussians what did German populations want within the country?

context: In <a0_0><b3_0>1939<b3_0/><a0_0/> the Regierungsbezirk Zichenau was annexed by Germany and incorporated into East Prussia. Parts of it were transferred to other regions, e.g. <a1_0>Suwałki to Regierungsbezirk Gumbinnen and Soldau to Regierungsbezirk Allenstein<a1_0/>. Despite Nazi propaganda presenting all of the regions annexed as possessing significant German populations that wanted <a2_0><b5_0>reunification<b5_0/> with Germany<a2_0/>, the Reich's statistics of late 1939 show that only 31,000 out of <b6_0>994,092<b6_0/> people in this territory were ethnic <b4_0>Germans<b4_0/>.[citation needed]
